</h3><p class="sc-dlWDvs hPuvxI pf-28_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-99690175-49cc-4452-b5e2-a494fd592853"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">As we enter the new year, many seek ways to embrace healthier habits and set positive goals. One impactful way to begin the year is by participating in Dry January, a month-long alcohol-free challenge spearheaded by Alcohol Change UK. With the 2025 theme focusing on the holistic benefits to your mind, body, and bank balance, Dry January presents a refreshing opportunity to reset and recharge.
</span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-jEABJj givtUl pf-31_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gvZzpm eSvBWp pf-32_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-EgOky kRKCTs pf-33_">What is Dry January?</h3><p class="sc-dlWDvs hPuvxI pf-35_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-5275e2a4-94fd-4928-934b-ec3c7162a8ac"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Dry January is a public health campaign encouraging individuals to abstain from alcohol in January. What started as a small initiative in 2013 has evolved into a global movement, with millions of participants reaping the benefits of taking a break from alcohol. By committing this, you’re supporting your well-being and contributing to a larger conversation about mindful drinking.
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-EgOky kRKCTs pf-38_">Key facts and statistics</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-fThTNe kChLHI pf-40_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-SrAaV esjcyJ pf-41_">Over 9 million people in the UK reported reducing their alcohol intake after participating in Dry January.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-SrAaV esjcyJ pf-43_">70% of participants reported better sleep quality and increased energy levels.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-SrAaV esjcyJ pf-45_">86% of people saved money during Dry January.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-SrAaV esjcyJ pf-47_">According to studies, 1 in 4 adults who take part in Dry January make lasting changes to their drinking habits.
</li></ul><p class="sc-dlWDvs hPuvxI pf-49_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-ebf37cad-d8ee-48cc-9ed3-c0dbff977562"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">These statistics highlight that Dry January isn’t just about a temporary detox. It’s a movement that can lead to long-term positive changes.</span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-jEABJj givtUl pf-52_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gvZzpm eSvBWp pf-53_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-EgOky kRKCTs pf-54_">Why join Dry January 2025?
</h3><p class="sc-dlWDvs hPuvxI pf-56_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-00b517ea-ae6b-4025-92b6-e406ec788715"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">This year’s campaign aims to highlight the positive changes you can experience, including:
</span></p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-fThTNe kChLHI pf-59_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-SrAaV esjcyJ pf-60_"><strong>Improved mental clarity</strong> - Studies have shown that alcohol can contribute to anxiety and disrupted sleep patterns. By removing alcohol from your daily routine, you may notice sharper focus, better sleep, and an overall uplift in your mood.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-SrAaV esjcyJ pf-62_"><strong>Physical health boost</strong> - After a month without alcohol, participants often report weight loss, reduced blood pressure, and improved liver function.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-SrAaV esjcyJ pf-64_"><strong>Financial savings </strong>- Alcohol can be an expensive habit. Alcohol-free can significantly reduce your spending, leaving you with extra savings for meaningful experiences or long-term goals.
</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-jEABJj givtUl pf-66_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gvZzpm eSvBWp pf-67_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-EgOky kRKCTs pf-68_">Tools to help you succeed</h3><p class="sc-dlWDvs hPuvxI pf-70_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-585d863a-bb83-4706-9198-08837dc6f783"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">To make the journey easier, Alcohol Change UK offers a variety of tools and resources, including:</span></p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-fThTNe kChLHI pf-73_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-SrAaV esjcyJ pf-74_"><strong>Try Dry® App </strong>- A free app to track your progress, log your milestones, and calculate your savings.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-SrAaV esjcyJ pf-76_"><strong>Alcohol-free recipes and tips</strong> - Access to delicious mocktail recipes and tips for socialising without alcohol.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-SrAaV esjcyJ pf-78_"><strong>Community support </strong>- Join online communities where participants share their Dry January stories, tips, and encouragement.
</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-jEABJj givtUl pf-80_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gvZzpm eSvBWp pf-81_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-EgOky kRKCTs pf-82_">Tips for navigating Dry January</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-fThTNe kChLHI pf-84_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-SrAaV esjcyJ pf-85_"><strong>Set your intention</strong> - Remind yourself of the reasons behind your decision. Having a clear purpose will keep you motivated, whether it’s for health, financial goals, or personal growth.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-SrAaV esjcyJ pf-87_"><strong>Plan ahead</strong> - Stock your home with alcohol-free alternatives and plan social outings where alcohol is not the focus.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-SrAaV esjcyJ pf-89_"><strong>Celebrate milestones</strong> - Reward yourself with small treats for each week you complete. Positive reinforcement can keep you on track.
